## ICP Fit Assessment

**Very strong fit.** Third-year CS, multiple project courses, has personally experienced the full failure cycle of trying to fix this himself.

---

## Interviewer Reflection

**Most important thing learned:**
The most technical student I have spoken to has the *least* hope. That is counterintuitive and important. We cannot assume technical users will be early adopters — they have been burned the most.

**What to do differently next time:**
Ask earlier about the *order* of tools tried. The chronology — from active builder to passive sufferer — was the most diagnostic part of the interview, and I almost missed it because I was asking about each tool separately.

